{"revision":"1360670485","tid":"f97489ea-6e87-11f1-8e5e-eebc344f8812","items":[{"title":"File:Meteosat-12-fci-march-equinox-2025-noon.jpg","leadImage":true,"section_id":0,"type":"image","showInGallery":true,"srcset":[{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2d/Meteosat-12-fci-march-equinox-2025-noon.jpg/500px-Meteosat-12-fci-march-equinox-2025-noon.jpg","scale":"1x"},{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2d/Meteosat-12-fci-march-equinox-2025-noon.jpg/1280px-Meteosat-12-fci-march-equinox-2025-noon.jpg","scale":"2x"}]},{"title":"File:The_Mysterious_Case_of_the_Disappearing_Dust.jpg","leadImage":false,"section_id":3,"type":"image","caption":{"html":"A depiction of the early <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Solar_System\" title=\"Solar System\" id=\"mwAZw\">Solar System</a>'s <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Protoplanetary_disk\" title=\"Protoplanetary disk\" id=\"mwAZ0\">protoplanetary disk</a> from which Earth and other Solar System bodies were formed","text":"A depiction of the early Solar System's protoplanetary disk from which Earth and other Solar System bodies were formed"},"showInGallery":true,"srcset":[{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2d/The_Mysterious_Case_of_the_Disappearing_Dust.jpg/500px-The_Mysterious_Case_of_the_Disappearing_Dust.jpg","scale":"1x"},{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2d/The_Mysterious_Case_of_the_Disappearing_Dust.jpg/1280px-The_Mysterious_Case_of_the_Disappearing_Dust.jpg","scale":"2x"}]},{"title":"File:NASA-EarlyEarth-PaleOrangeDot-20190802.jpg","leadImage":false,"section_id":4,"type":"image","caption":{"html":"<i id=\"mwAfs\">Pale orange dot</i>, an impression of <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Early_Earth\" title=\"Early Earth\" id=\"mwAfw\">Early Earth</a>, featuring its tinted orange <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Methane\" title=\"Methane\" id=\"mwAf0\">methane</a>-rich <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Prebiotic_atmosphere\" title=\"Prebiotic atmosphere\" id=\"mwAf4\">early atmosphere</a><sup about=\"#mwt175\" class=\"mw-ref reference\" id=\"cite_ref-Trainer_Pavlov_DeWitt_Jimenez_pp._18035–18042_51-0\" rel=\"dc:references\" typeof=\"mw:Extension/ref\" data-mw=\"{&quot;name&quot;:&quot;ref&quot;,&quot;attrs&quot;:{&quot;name&quot;:&quot;Trainer Pavlov DeWitt Jimenez pp. 18035–18042&quot;},&quot;body&quot;:{&quot;id&quot;:&quot;mw-reference-text-cite_note-Trainer_Pavlov_DeWitt_Jimenez_pp._18035–18042-51&quot;}}\"><a href=\"./Earth#cite_note-Trainer_Pavlov_DeWitt_Jimenez_pp._18035–18042-51\" id=\"mwAf8\"><span class=\"mw-reflink-text\" id=\"mwAgA\"><span class=\"cite-bracket\" id=\"mwAgE\">[</span>47<span class=\"cite-bracket\" id=\"mwAgI\">]</span></span></a></sup>","text":"Pale orange dot, an impression of Early Earth, featuring its tinted orange methane-rich early atmosphere[47]"},"showInGallery":true,"srcset":[{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9b/NASA-EarlyEarth-PaleOrangeDot-20190802.jpg/500px-NASA-EarlyEarth-PaleOrangeDot-20190802.jpg","scale":"1x"},{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9b/NASA-EarlyEarth-PaleOrangeDot-20190802.jpg/1280px-NASA-EarlyEarth-PaleOrangeDot-20190802.jpg","scale":"2x"}]},{"title":"File:Archean.png","leadImage":false,"section_id":5,"type":"image","caption":{"html":"An impression of the <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Archean\" title=\"Archean\" id=\"mwAlo\">Archean</a>, the <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Geologic_time_scale#Divisions_of_geologic_time\" title=\"Geologic time scale\" id=\"mwAls\">eon</a> after Earth's formation, featuring round <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Stromatolite\" title=\"Stromatolite\" id=\"mwAlw\">stromatolites</a>, which are early oxygen-producing forms of life from billions of years ago. After the <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Late_Heavy_Bombardment\" title=\"Late Heavy Bombardment\" id=\"mwAl0\">Late Heavy Bombardment</a>, <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Earth's_crust\" title=\"Earth's crust\" id=\"mwAl4\">Earth's crust</a> had cooled, its water-rich barren <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Planetary_surface\" title=\"Planetary surface\" id=\"mwAl8\">surface</a> is marked by <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Continent\" title=\"Continent\" id=\"mwAmA\">continents</a> and <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Volcano\" title=\"Volcano\" id=\"mwAmE\">volcanoes</a>, with the Moon still orbiting Earth half as far as it is today, appearing 2.8 times larger and producing strong <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Tide\" title=\"Tide\" id=\"mwAmI\">tides</a>.<sup about=\"#mwt206\" class=\"mw-ref reference\" id=\"cite_ref-Lunar_and_Planetary_Institute_64-0\" rel=\"dc:references\" typeof=\"mw:Extension/ref\" data-mw=\"{&quot;name&quot;:&quot;ref&quot;,&quot;attrs&quot;:{&quot;name&quot;:&quot;Lunar and Planetary Institute&quot;},&quot;body&quot;:{&quot;id&quot;:&quot;mw-reference-text-cite_note-Lunar_and_Planetary_Institute-64&quot;}}\"><a href=\"./Earth#cite_note-Lunar_and_Planetary_Institute-64\" id=\"mwAmM\"><span class=\"mw-reflink-text\" id=\"mwAmQ\"><span class=\"cite-bracket\" id=\"mwAmU\">[</span>60<span class=\"cite-bracket\" id=\"mwAmY\">]</span></span></a></sup>","text":"An impression of the Archean, the eon after Earth's formation, featuring round stromatolites, which are early oxygen-producing forms of life from billions of years ago. After the Late Heavy Bombardment, Earth's crust had cooled, its water-rich barren surface is marked by continents and volcanoes, with the Moon still orbiting Earth half as far as it is today, appearing 2.8 times larger and producing strong tides.[60]"},"showInGallery":true,"srcset":[{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f2/Archean.png/500px-Archean.png","scale":"1x"},{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f2/Archean.png/1280px-Archean.png","scale":"2x"}]},{"title":"File:Red_Giant_Earth_warm.jpg","leadImage":false,"section_id":6,"type":"image","caption":{"html":"A conception of the scorched Earth after the <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Sun\" title=\"Sun\" id=\"mwAuA\">Sun</a> has entered the <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Red_giant\" title=\"Red giant\" id=\"mwAuE\">red giant</a> phase, about 5–7<span typeof=\"mw:Entity\" id=\"mwAuI\">&nbsp;</span>billion years in the future","text":"A conception of the scorched Earth after the Sun has entered the red giant phase, about 5–7 billion years in the future"},"showInGallery":true,"srcset":[{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/aa/Red_Giant_Earth_warm.jpg/500px-Red_Giant_Earth_warm.jpg","scale":"1x"}]},{"title":"File:Terrestrial_planet_size_comp_2024.png","leadImage":false,"section_id":7,"type":"image","caption":{"html":"Earth depicted to scale alongside the <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Planetary-mass_object\" title=\"Planetary-mass object\" id=\"mwAyc\">planetary-mass objects</a> of the <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Inner_Solar_System\" title=\"Inner Solar System\" class=\"mw-redirect\" id=\"mwAyg\">Inner Solar System</a>. From left: <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Mercury_(planet)\" title=\"Mercury (planet)\" id=\"mwAyk\">Mercury</a>, <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Venus\" title=\"Venus\" id=\"mwAyo\">Venus</a>, Earth, the <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Moon\" title=\"Moon\" id=\"mwAys\">Moon</a>, <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Mars\" title=\"Mars\" id=\"mwAyw\">Mars</a> and <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Ceres_(dwarf_planet)\" title=\"Ceres (dwarf planet)\" id=\"mwAy0\">Ceres</a>.","text":"Earth depicted to scale alongside the planetary-mass objects of the Inner Solar System. From left: Mercury, Venus, Earth, the Moon, Mars and Ceres."},"showInGallery":true,"srcset":[{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1d/Terrestrial_planet_size_comp_2024.png/500px-Terrestrial_planet_size_comp_2024.png","scale":"1x"}]},{"title":"File:Earth-cutaway-schematic-english.svg","leadImage":false,"section_id":9,"type":"image","caption":{"html":"","text":""},"showInGallery":true,"srcset":[{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e9/Earth_cutaway_schematic-en.svg/500px-Earth_cutaway_schematic-en.svg.png","scale":"1x"}]},{"title":"File:Earth_heat_flow.jpg","leadImage":false,"section_id":10,"type":"image","caption":{"html":"A map of <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Heat_flow\" title=\"Heat flow\" class=\"mw-redirect\" id=\"mwA9w\">heat flow</a> from Earth's interior to the surface of Earth's crust, mostly along the <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Oceanic_ridge\" title=\"Oceanic ridge\" class=\"mw-redirect\" id=\"mwA90\">oceanic ridges</a>","text":"A map of heat flow from Earth's interior to the surface of Earth's crust, mostly along the oceanic ridges"},"showInGallery":true,"srcset":[{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/74/Earth_heat_flow.jpg/500px-Earth_heat_flow.jpg","scale":"1x"}]},{"title":"File:Tectonic_plates_2022.svg","leadImage":false,"section_id":11,"type":"image","caption":{"html":"Map of Earth's <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./List_of_tectonic_plates\" title=\"List of tectonic plates\" id=\"mwBBs\">16 principal tectonic plates</a>","text":"Map of Earth's 16 principal tectonic plates"},"showInGallery":true,"srcset":[{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/67/Tectonic_plates_%282022%29.svg/500px-Tectonic_plates_%282022%29.svg.png","scale":"1x"},{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/67/Tectonic_plates_%282022%29.svg/1280px-Tectonic_plates_%282022%29.svg.png","scale":"2x"}]},{"title":"File:AYool_topography_15min.png","leadImage":false,"section_id":12,"type":"image","caption":{"html":"<a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Topographic_relief\" title=\"Topographic relief\" class=\"mw-redirect\" id=\"mwBGQ\">Topographic relief</a> map of <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Earth's_crust\" title=\"Earth's crust\" id=\"mwBGU\">Earth's crust</a>","text":"Topographic relief map of Earth's crust"},"showInGallery":true,"srcset":[{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/24/AYool_topography_15min.png/500px-AYool_topography_15min.png","scale":"1x"},{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/24/AYool_topography_15min.png/1280px-AYool_topography_15min.png","scale":"2x"}]},{"title":"File:Global_View_of_the_Arctic_and_Antarctic.jpg","leadImage":false,"section_id":13,"type":"image","caption":{"html":"A <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Compositing\" title=\"Compositing\" id=\"mwBJQ\">composite</a> image of Earth with an opaque cloud cover, making the different types of surface discernible: Earth's surface dominating Ocean (blue), Africa with lush (green) to dry (brown) land and Earth's polar ice in the form of <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Antarctic_sea_ice\" title=\"Antarctic sea ice\" id=\"mwBJU\">Antarctic sea ice</a> (grey) covering the <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Southern_Ocean\" title=\"Southern Ocean\" id=\"mwBJY\">Antarctic or Southern Ocean</a> and the <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Antarctic_ice_sheet\" title=\"Antarctic ice sheet\" id=\"mwBJc\">Antarctic ice sheet</a> (white) covering <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Antarctica\" title=\"Antarctica\" id=\"mwBJg\">Antarctica</a>.","text":"A composite image of Earth with an opaque cloud cover, making the different types of surface discernible: Earth's surface dominating Ocean (blue), Africa with lush (green) to dry (brown) land and Earth's polar ice in the form of Antarctic sea ice (grey) covering the Antarctic or Southern Ocean and the Antarctic ice sheet (white) covering Antarctica."},"showInGallery":true,"srcset":[{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3e/Global_View_of_the_Arctic_and_Antarctic.jpg/500px-Global_View_of_the_Arctic_and_Antarctic.jpg","scale":"1x"},{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3e/Global_View_of_the_Arctic_and_Antarctic.jpg/1280px-Global_View_of_the_Arctic_and_Antarctic.jpg","scale":"2x"}]},{"title":"File:Magnetosphere_Levels-en.svg","leadImage":false,"section_id":17,"type":"image","caption":{"html":"A schematic view of Earth's magnetosphere with <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Solar_wind\" title=\"Solar wind\" id=\"mwBXs\">solar wind</a> flowing from left to right","text":"A schematic view of Earth's magnetosphere with solar wind flowing from left to right"},"showInGallery":true,"srcset":[{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2d/Magnetosphere_Levels-en.svg/250px-Magnetosphere_Levels-en.svg.png","scale":"1x"},{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2d/Magnetosphere_Levels-en.svg/500px-Magnetosphere_Levels-en.svg.png","scale":"2x"}]},{"title":"File:MarsReconnaissanceOrbiter-Views-EarthMoon-20220422.jpg","leadImage":false,"section_id":20,"type":"image","caption":{"html":"Earth and the Moon as seen from <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Mars\" title=\"Mars\" id=\"mwBd8\">Mars</a> by the <i id=\"mwBeA\"><a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Mars_Reconnaissance_Orbiter\" title=\"Mars Reconnaissance Orbiter\" id=\"mwBeE\">Mars Reconnaissance Orbiter</a></i>","text":"Earth and the Moon as seen from Mars by the Mars Reconnaissance Orbiter"},"showInGallery":true,"srcset":[{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0c/MarsReconnaissanceOrbiter-Views-EarthMoon-20220422.jpg/500px-MarsReconnaissanceOrbiter-Views-EarthMoon-20220422.jpg","scale":"1x"}]},{"title":"File:Debris-GEO1280.jpg","leadImage":false,"section_id":21,"type":"image","caption":{"html":"A computer-generated image mapping the prevalence of <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Artificial_satellite\" title=\"Artificial satellite\" class=\"mw-redirect\" id=\"mwBlE\">artificial satellites</a> and <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Space_debris\" title=\"Space debris\" id=\"mwBlI\">space debris</a> around Earth in <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Geosynchronous_orbit\" title=\"Geosynchronous orbit\" id=\"mwBlM\">geosynchronous</a> and <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Low_Earth_orbit\" title=\"Low Earth orbit\" id=\"mwBlQ\">low Earth orbit</a>","text":"A computer-generated image mapping the prevalence of artificial satellites and space debris around Earth in geosynchronous and low Earth orbit"},"showInGallery":true,"srcset":[{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a1/Debris-GEO1280.jpg/500px-Debris-GEO1280.jpg","scale":"1x"}]},{"title":"File:EpicEarth-Globespin-tilt-23.4.gif","leadImage":false,"section_id":23,"type":"image","caption":{"html":"Satellite <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Time-lapse_photography\" title=\"Time-lapse photography\" id=\"mwBo0\">time-lapse imagery</a> of Earth's rotation showing axis tilt","text":"Satellite time-lapse imagery of Earth's rotation showing axis tilt"},"showInGallery":true,"srcset":[{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a0/EpicEarth-Globespin-tilt-23.4.gif/500px-EpicEarth-Globespin-tilt-23.4.gif","scale":"1x"},{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a0/EpicEarth-Globespin-tilt-23.4.gif/1280px-EpicEarth-Globespin-tilt-23.4.gif","scale":"2x"}]},{"title":"File:Seasons1.svg","leadImage":false,"section_id":24,"type":"image","caption":{"html":"Exaggerated illustration of Earth's elliptical orbit around the Sun, marking that the orbital extreme points (<a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Apoapsis\" title=\"Apoapsis\" class=\"mw-redirect\" id=\"mwBsw\">apoapsis</a> and <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Periapsis\" title=\"Periapsis\" class=\"mw-redirect\" id=\"mwBs0\">periapsis</a>) are not the same as the four seasonal extreme points, the <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Equinox\" title=\"Equinox\" id=\"mwBs4\">equinox</a> and <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Solstice\" title=\"Solstice\" id=\"mwBs8\">solstice</a>","text":"Exaggerated illustration of Earth's elliptical orbit around the Sun, marking that the orbital extreme points (apoapsis and periapsis) are not the same as the four seasonal extreme points, the equinox and solstice"},"showInGallery":true,"srcset":[{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f0/Seasons1.svg/500px-Seasons1.svg.png","scale":"1x"},{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f0/Seasons1.svg/1280px-Seasons1.svg.png","scale":"2x"}]},{"title":"File:Axial_tilt_vs_tropical_and_polar_circles.svg","leadImage":false,"section_id":25,"type":"image","caption":{"html":"Earth's axial tilt causing different angles of seasonal illumination at different orbital positions around the Sun","text":"Earth's axial tilt causing different angles of seasonal illumination at different orbital positions around the Sun"},"showInGallery":true,"srcset":[{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/40/Axial_tilt_vs_tropical_and_polar_circles.svg/500px-Axial_tilt_vs_tropical_and_polar_circles.svg.png","scale":"1x"}]},{"title":"File:ISS-42_Waning_sun.jpg","leadImage":false,"section_id":26,"type":"image","caption":{"html":"A view of the <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Southern_Pacific\" title=\"Southern Pacific\" class=\"mw-redirect\" id=\"mwB0o\">Southern Pacific</a> under <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Moonlight\" title=\"Moonlight\" id=\"mwB0s\">moonlight</a> with different layers of Earth's atmosphere visible: the <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Troposphere\" title=\"Troposphere\" id=\"mwB0w\">troposphere</a> with its clouds casting shadows, a band of <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Stratospheric\" title=\"Stratospheric\" class=\"mw-redirect\" id=\"mwB00\">stratospheric</a> blue sky at the horizon, and a line of green <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Airglow\" title=\"Airglow\" id=\"mwB04\">airglow</a> of the lower <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Thermosphere\" title=\"Thermosphere\" id=\"mwB08\">thermosphere</a> around an <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Kármán_line\" title=\"Kármán line\" id=\"mwB1A\">altitude of 100<span typeof=\"mw:Entity\" id=\"mwB1E\">&nbsp;</span>km, at the edge of space</a>","text":"A view of the Southern Pacific under moonlight with different layers of Earth's atmosphere visible: the troposphere with its clouds casting shadows, a band of stratospheric blue sky at the horizon, and a line of green airglow of the lower thermosphere around an altitude of 100 km, at the edge of space"},"showInGallery":true,"srcset":[{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/97/ISS-42_Waning_sun.jpg/500px-ISS-42_Waning_sun.jpg","scale":"1x"},{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/97/ISS-42_Waning_sun.jpg/1280px-ISS-42_Waning_sun.jpg","scale":"2x"}]},{"title":"File:Antarctic_aurora_ESA313457.jpg","leadImage":false,"section_id":28,"type":"image","caption":{"html":"Earth's night-side upper atmosphere appearing from the bottom as bands of <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Afterglow\" title=\"Afterglow\" id=\"mwB7o\">afterglow</a> illuminating the <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Troposphere\" title=\"Troposphere\" id=\"mwB7s\">troposphere</a> in orange with silhouettes of clouds, and the <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Stratosphere\" title=\"Stratosphere\" id=\"mwB7w\">stratosphere</a> in white and blue. Next the <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Mesosphere\" title=\"Mesosphere\" id=\"mwB70\">mesosphere</a> (pink area) extends to the orange and faintly green line of the lowest <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Airglow\" title=\"Airglow\" id=\"mwB74\">airglow</a>, at about one hundred kilometers at the <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Outer_space#Boundary\" title=\"Outer space\" id=\"mwB78\">edge of space</a> and the lower edge of the <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Thermosphere\" title=\"Thermosphere\" id=\"mwB8A\">thermosphere</a> (invisible). Continuing with green and red bands of <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Aurora\" title=\"Aurora\" id=\"mwB8E\">aurorae</a> stretching over several hundred kilometers.","text":"Earth's night-side upper atmosphere appearing from the bottom as bands of afterglow illuminating the troposphere in orange with silhouettes of clouds, and the stratosphere in white and blue. Next the mesosphere (pink area) extends to the orange and faintly green line of the lowest airglow, at about one hundred kilometers at the edge of space and the lower edge of the thermosphere (invisible). Continuing with green and red bands of aurorae stretching over several hundred kilometers."},"showInGallery":true,"srcset":[{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/78/Antarctic_aurora_ESA313457.jpg/500px-Antarctic_aurora_ESA313457.jpg","scale":"1x"},{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/78/Antarctic_aurora_ESA313457.jpg/1280px-Antarctic_aurora_ESA313457.jpg","scale":"2x"}]},{"title":"File:IntertropicalConvergenceZone-EO.jpg","leadImage":false,"section_id":30,"type":"image","caption":{"html":"The <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./ITCZ\" title=\"ITCZ\" class=\"mw-redirect\" id=\"mwCAc\">ITCZ</a>'s band of clouds over the Eastern Pacific and the Americas as seen from space","text":"The ITCZ's band of clouds over the Eastern Pacific and the Americas as seen from space"},"showInGallery":true,"srcset":[{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/12/IntertropicalConvergenceZone-EO.jpg/500px-IntertropicalConvergenceZone-EO.jpg","scale":"1x"},{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/12/IntertropicalConvergenceZone-EO.jpg/1280px-IntertropicalConvergenceZone-EO.jpg","scale":"2x"}]},{"title":"File:Köppen-Geiger_Climate_Classification_Map_(1980–2016)_no_borders.png","leadImage":false,"section_id":30,"type":"image","caption":{"html":"Worldwide <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Köppen_climate_classification\" title=\"Köppen climate classification\" id=\"mwCEQ\">Köppen climate classifications</a>","text":"Worldwide Köppen climate classifications"},"showInGallery":true,"srcset":[{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/32/K%C3%B6ppen-Geiger_Climate_Classification_Map_%281980%E2%80%932016%29_no_borders.png/500px-K%C3%B6ppen-Geiger_Climate_Classification_Map_%281980%E2%80%932016%29_no_borders.png","scale":"1x"},{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/32/K%C3%B6ppen-Geiger_Climate_Classification_Map_%281980%E2%80%932016%29_no_borders.png/1280px-K%C3%B6ppen-Geiger_Climate_Classification_Map_%281980%E2%80%932016%29_no_borders.png","scale":"2x"}]},{"title":"File:Ocean_world_Earth.jpg","leadImage":false,"section_id":31,"type":"image","caption":{"html":"A view of Earth with its <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Global_ocean\" title=\"Global ocean\" class=\"mw-redirect\" id=\"mwCGw\">global ocean</a> and <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Cloud_cover\" title=\"Cloud cover\" id=\"mwCG0\">cloud cover</a>, which dominate Earth's surface and <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Hydrosphere\" title=\"Hydrosphere\" id=\"mwCG4\">hydrosphere</a>; at Earth's <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Polar_regions_of_Earth\" title=\"Polar regions of Earth\" id=\"mwCG8\">polar</a> regions, its hydrosphere forms larger areas of ice cover.","text":"A view of Earth with its global ocean and cloud cover, which dominate Earth's surface and hydrosphere; at Earth's polar regions, its hydrosphere forms larger areas of ice cover."},"showInGallery":true,"srcset":[{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f6/Ocean_world_Earth.jpg/500px-Ocean_world_Earth.jpg","scale":"1x"},{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f6/Ocean_world_Earth.jpg/1280px-Ocean_world_Earth.jpg","scale":"2x"}]},{"title":"File:Mollweide_Cycle.gif","leadImage":false,"section_id":32,"type":"image","caption":{"html":"An animation of the changing density of <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Primary_production\" title=\"Primary production\" id=\"mwCN4\">productive</a> vegetation on land (low in brown; heavy in dark green) and phytoplankton at the <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Ocean_surface\" title=\"Ocean surface\" class=\"mw-redirect\" id=\"mwCN8\">ocean surface</a> (low in purple; high in yellow)","text":"An animation of the changing density of productive vegetation on land (low in brown; heavy in dark green) and phytoplankton at the ocean surface (low in purple; high in yellow)"},"showInGallery":true,"srcset":[{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1d/Mollweide_Cycle.gif/500px-Mollweide_Cycle.gif","scale":"1x"}]},{"title":"File:BlackMarble20161km.jpg","leadImage":false,"section_id":34,"type":"image","caption":{"html":"A composite image of <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Light_pollution\" title=\"Light pollution\" id=\"mwCUc\">artificial light emissions</a> at night on a map of Earth","text":"A composite image of artificial light emissions at night on a map of Earth"},"showInGallery":true,"srcset":[{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/af/BlackMarble20161km.jpg/500px-BlackMarble20161km.jpg","scale":"1x"},{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/af/BlackMarble20161km.jpg/1280px-BlackMarble20161km.jpg","scale":"2x"}]},{"title":"File:Flag_of_the_United_Nations.svg","leadImage":false,"section_id":34,"type":"image","caption":{"html":"The <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Flag_of_the_United_Nations\" title=\"Flag of the United Nations\" id=\"mwCYI\">flag</a> of the <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./United_Nations\" title=\"United Nations\" id=\"mwCYM\">United Nations</a>","text":"The flag of the United Nations"},"showInGallery":true,"srcset":[{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2f/Flag_of_the_United_Nations.svg/500px-Flag_of_the_United_Nations.svg.png","scale":"1x"}]},{"title":"File:Global_land_use_for_food_production,_OWID_statistic.png","leadImage":false,"section_id":35,"type":"image","caption":{"html":"Earth's land use for human agriculture in 2019","text":"Earth's land use for human agriculture in 2019"},"showInGallery":true,"srcset":[{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/74/Global_land_use_for_food_production%2C_OWID_statistic.png/500px-Global_land_use_for_food_production%2C_OWID_statistic.png","scale":"1x"},{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/74/Global_land_use_for_food_production%2C_OWID_statistic.png/1280px-Global_land_use_for_food_production%2C_OWID_statistic.png","scale":"2x"}]},{"title":"File:Global_Temperature_And_Forces_With_Fahrenheit.svg","leadImage":false,"section_id":36,"type":"image","caption":{"html":"Overall increase in average surface air temperature juxtaposed with natural drivers: human activity has caused increased temperatures, with natural forces adding some variability.<sup about=\"#mwt881\" class=\"mw-ref reference\" id=\"cite_ref-284\" rel=\"dc:references\" typeof=\"mw:Extension/ref\" data-mw=\"{&quot;name&quot;:&quot;ref&quot;,&quot;attrs&quot;:{},&quot;body&quot;:{&quot;id&quot;:&quot;mw-reference-text-cite_note-284&quot;}}\"><a href=\"./Earth#cite_note-284\" id=\"mwCd8\"><span class=\"mw-reflink-text\" id=\"mwCeA\"><span class=\"cite-bracket\" id=\"mwCeE\">[</span>273<span class=\"cite-bracket\" id=\"mwCeI\">]</span></span></a></sup><sup about=\"#mwt884\" class=\"mw-ref reference\" id=\"cite_ref-285\" rel=\"dc:references\" typeof=\"mw:Extension/ref\" data-mw=\"{&quot;name&quot;:&quot;ref&quot;,&quot;attrs&quot;:{},&quot;body&quot;:{&quot;id&quot;:&quot;mw-reference-text-cite_note-285&quot;}}\"><a href=\"./Earth#cite_note-285\" id=\"mwCeM\"><span class=\"mw-reflink-text\" id=\"mwCeQ\"><span class=\"cite-bracket\" id=\"mwCeU\">[</span>274<span class=\"cite-bracket\" id=\"mwCeY\">]</span></span></a></sup>","text":"Overall increase in average surface air temperature juxtaposed with natural drivers: human activity has caused increased temperatures, with natural forces adding some variability.[273][274]"},"showInGallery":true,"srcset":[{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/08/Global_Temperature_And_Forces_With_Fahrenheit.svg/500px-Global_Temperature_And_Forces_With_Fahrenheit.svg.png","scale":"1x"}]},{"title":"File:Islamic_cosmology.jpg","leadImage":false,"section_id":37,"type":"image","caption":{"html":"A combination of different cosmological <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Middle_Eastern\" title=\"Middle Eastern\" class=\"mw-redirect\" id=\"mwChU\">Middle Eastern</a> <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Axis_mundi\" title=\"Axis mundi\" id=\"mwChY\">axis mundi</a> ideas from the <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Post-classical_age\" title=\"Post-classical age\" class=\"mw-redirect\" id=\"mwChc\">post-classical age</a> (<a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./ʿAjā'ib_al-makhlūqāt_wa_gharā'ib_al-mawjūdāt\" title=\"ʿAjā'ib al-makhlūqāt wa gharā'ib al-mawjūdāt\" class=\"mw-redirect\" id=\"mwChg\"><i id=\"mwChk\">The Wonders of Creation</i></a> by <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Zakariya_al-Qazwini\" title=\"Zakariya al-Qazwini\" id=\"mwCho\">Zakariya al-Qazwini</a>) showing a flat round Earth surrounded by a range of <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Mount_Qaf\" title=\"Mount Qaf\" id=\"mwChs\">Qaf Mountains</a>, resting on the back of a giant bull (<a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Kujata\" title=\"Kujata\" id=\"mwChw\">Kujata</a> or <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Behemoth\" title=\"Behemoth\" id=\"mwCh0\">Behemoth</a>), which in turn stands on a vast fish (<a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Bahamut\" title=\"Bahamut\" id=\"mwCh4\">Bahamut</a> or <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Leviathan\" title=\"Leviathan\" id=\"mwCh8\">Leviathan</a>) in a <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Cosmic_ocean\" title=\"Cosmic ocean\" id=\"mwCiA\">cosmic ocean</a> held up by an angel or <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"./Jinn\" title=\"Jinn\" id=\"mwCiE\">jinn</a><sup about=\"#mwt907\" class=\"mw-ref reference\" id=\"cite_ref-v005_291-0\" rel=\"dc:references\" typeof=\"mw:Extension/ref\" data-mw=\"{&quot;name&quot;:&quot;ref&quot;,&quot;attrs&quot;:{&quot;name&quot;:&quot;v005&quot;},&quot;body&quot;:{&quot;id&quot;:&quot;mw-reference-text-cite_note-v005-291&quot;}}\"><a href=\"./Earth#cite_note-v005-291\" id=\"mwCiI\"><span class=\"mw-reflink-text\" id=\"mwCiM\"><span class=\"cite-bracket\" id=\"mwCiQ\">[</span>280<span class=\"cite-bracket\" id=\"mwCiU\">]</span></span></a></sup><sup about=\"#mwt910\" class=\"mw-ref reference\" id=\"cite_ref-Lebling_292-0\" rel=\"dc:references\" typeof=\"mw:Extension/ref\" data-mw=\"{&quot;name&quot;:&quot;ref&quot;,&quot;attrs&quot;:{&quot;name&quot;:&quot;Lebling&quot;},&quot;body&quot;:{&quot;id&quot;:&quot;mw-reference-text-cite_note-Lebling-292&quot;}}\"><a href=\"./Earth#cite_note-Lebling-292\" id=\"mwCiY\"><span class=\"mw-reflink-text\" id=\"mwCic\"><span class=\"cite-bracket\" id=\"mwCig\">[</span>281<span class=\"cite-bracket\" id=\"mwCik\">]</span></span></a></sup>","text":"A combination of different cosmological Middle Eastern axis mundi ideas from the post-classical age (The Wonders of Creation by Zakariya al-Qazwini) showing a flat round Earth surrounded by a range of Qaf Mountains, resting on the back of a giant bull (Kujata or Behemoth), which in turn stands on a vast fish (Bahamut or Leviathan) in a cosmic ocean held up by an angel or jinn[280][281]"},"showInGallery":true,"srcset":[{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/67/Islamic_cosmology.jpg/330px-Islamic_cosmology.jpg","scale":"1x"}]},{"title":"File:The_Blue_Marble,_AS17-148-22727.jpg","leadImage":false,"section_id":37,"type":"image","gallery_id":"mwCpM","showInGallery":true,"srcset":[{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/70/The_Blue_Marble%2C_AS17-148-22727.jpg/250px-The_Blue_Marble%2C_AS17-148-22727.jpg","scale":"1x"},{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/70/The_Blue_Marble%2C_AS17-148-22727.jpg/500px-The_Blue_Marble%2C_AS17-148-22727.jpg","scale":"2x"}]},{"title":"File:Earth_From_the_Perspective_of_Artemis_II.jpg","leadImage":false,"section_id":37,"type":"image","gallery_id":"mwCpM","showInGallery":true,"srcset":[{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/63/Earth_From_the_Perspective_of_Artemis_II.jpg/250px-Earth_From_the_Perspective_of_Artemis_II.jpg","scale":"1x"},{"src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/63/Earth_From_the_Perspective_of_Artemis_II.jpg/500px-Earth_From_the_Perspective_of_Artemis_II.jpg","scale":"2x"}]},{"title":"File:Hello-earth-looped-closeups.webm","leadImage":false,"section_id":37,"type":"video